    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive outlook, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez**, who leads the squad with an elite score of 86.40. His massive projection is bolstered by a significant park factor (+16%) that creates an ideal environment for his power profile against the right-handed matchup. Joining him as a top-tier start is **Trea Turner** (74.91), whose value remains magnified by our league\u2019s priority on stolen bases; even with a tough matchup, his elite speed and primary spot in the batting order make him a foundational piece. Additionally, keep an eye on **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (77.86), whose score is heavily inflated by a favorable matchup against a pitcher with a slow delivery, providing the perfect storm for him to exploit the stolen base category despite his projected spot at the bottom of the order.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the marginal slot occupied by **Luke Raley** (45.32). While **Chase Meidroth** (44.31) was the closest contender on the bench, **Luke Raley** ultimately earned the nod due to his superior platoon edge and the added potential for stolen bases against a pitcher with a slow delivery. While **Dillon Dingler** (63.75) offers a strong play at catcher, we remain cautious regarding **Gary Sanchez** (47.55), who faces an uncertainty flag with his lineup position currently pending. Managers should note that **Christian Yelich**, **Zac Veen**, and **Colt Keith** remain unavailable, keeping our depth limited as we navigate this stretch. Given the high reliance on **Kyle Schwarber** (73.00) and **Junior Caminero** (72.82) to maintain our momentum in runs and RBI, the success of the Zebras today hinges on these high-ceiling power bats capitalizing on their favorable platoon advantages.",
